body.description: The Summit X3 jogging stroller offers exceptional performance and maneuverability on any terrain. This 3 wheel stroller and jogger hybrid is conveniently equipped with an all new remote swivel lock that is mounted on the handlebar. Simply flip the lever to lock the front wheel straight when you're off for a run or release to swivel mode in one step for walking without having to touch the front wheel. This stroller features Baby Jogger's patented quick fold technology so you can fold the Summit X3 with one hand, the universal accessory mounting bracket to accessorize with ease, an improved all wheel independent suspension system and hand operated rear drum brakes offer increased control for added safety on hilly terrain. The Summit X3 sports 16" rear and 12" front quick release pneumatic tires, a padded seat that reclines to a near flat position and a vented seat top with weather cover to increase airflow within the stroller when reclined. Also featured is a large adjustable sun canopy with peek a boo windows and side ventilation panels, an comfortable handlebar with wipe clean grip, a seat back storage compartment, a large under seat basket, adjustable five point safety harness with shoulder pads and a rear parking brake. The Summit X3 is a great solution for parents who want one stroller that does it all while maintaining all the style and safety you'd expect from Baby Jogger. Maximum weight capacity is 75 pounds.

Since 1984, the company has been inspired by children and the potential to create ingenious solutions for everyday problems. That means helping parents and their children be more places and see more things. From the City Mini line and Summit X3 to the City Select, Baby Jogger offers a stroller for every terrain and every need. So parents and children can easily live active lives everyday. Wheel Lock The Summit X3 jogging stroller offers a remote wheel lock on the handlebar that lets you switch between swivel mode and a locked position for the front wheel. Switching between running and just running errands is now at your fingertips.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 11, 2017
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great stroller for active parents and picky babies.
reviews.reviewText: Great suspension! I use it with a Britax B-Safe 35 Elite car seat with an adapter by Baby Jogger. The adapter is rock solid and the stroller is excellent. I bought it on sale and it is worth it.The lower storage is a little tight for urban parents in general, but it is made for running outdoors not errands. Works wonderfully with added storage and it is a breeze to fold. The large rear wheels can be a little bulky for a lot of car trunks but the can be easily removed with two well made latches. This allows the stroller to fold up tighter and you can stack the wheels next to it. ( Just be sure to point both spindles toward each other so that they are protected by the wheel spokes.The only thing that bugs me is the plastic for viewing our baby is foggy. ( Not sure how to best clean it..) But I'm sure we can fix it.All in all GREAT product well worth the sale price.MSRP is a high for me. I paid around 290 for it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Love this stroller!
reviews.reviewText: This is the perfect stroller for me and my little one! Really easy to maneuver and I get complements all the time when other people push it for how well the shock absorbers work! I really like the brake (haven't had to use it) and the hand strap on the side (I use this all the time). The bottom doesn't hold a lot of cargo, but the diaper bag will fit under so it's enough for me! I've even taken it running and I felt it did really well and baby didn't get too jostled.My only complaint is even thought it says it is one handed....you have to be really strong to lift it into a car trunk or into a hall closet one handed. I have always had to put baby down and then move the stroller folded.This even worked great when baby was less than 6 months (started probably at 3 months) because of the almost flat setting. We took a neck pillow from one of her bouncers and used it in the stroller so her head was supported.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 17, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good stroller for walks and jogs
reviews.reviewText: I love this stroller, it is so smooth and easy to maneuver. My baby girl is happy in it. Two peek a boo windows to see baby and a few mesh windows for air flow. The basket is okay size, big enough for the essentials. There is a mesh pocket in the back for a water bottle, phone and keys but no cup holder. The suspension is great. My only issue with this is that its heavy for me to carry and I still cant figure out how to keep it upright when folded.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 1, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great stroller, but needed maintenance straight out of the box
reviews.reviewText: This is a great stroller. I did a lot of research on jogging strollers before selecting this one. This stroller rides super smooth and is easy to push. I love that it goes up to a 75 lb weight limit, too.The reason why I am not giving it a five star review, which I really want to, it's because it needed some pretty serious maintenance right out of the box. When I took it for its first run, I was about a mile out on a paved trail and the wheels started squeaking SO loudly that I honestly think you could have heard me within a half mile radius. It was so loud that you really couldn't run with it and instead needed to book it back to the car. It needed oil in the wheel bearings. I have had to lubricate the wheel bearings three times, on three separate days, to get the squeaking under control. It is fixed now but for the cost of this stroller, I really don't think it's right that it immediately needed maintenance to be usable.Structurally, the stroller is in great shape, and I would recommend it to someone else, just be aware that you might need to oil the wheel bearings as soon as you unbox it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 11, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Jogging stroller for Grandma!
reviews.reviewText: I am 5’9” and wanted a stroller that felt comfortable for me. I am not a runner but I love the height of the stroller and how smooth it rides. It is also easy to collapse. The buckles are bit challenging for people who need readers. I can’t see well enough to try to wrangle an 8 month old into the stroller and get the 4 buckles (2 on each side) in place before the little guy wriggles out of the straps and stands up. I hope to get better with practice !

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Absolutely love this stroller!!
reviews.reviewText: I had this same stroller in the double version several years ago and absolutely loved it. I've checked several times over the years and the single version seemed to be out of stock from every retailer I checked. With #4 on the way soon I decided to check again, and suddenly it was back in stock, so we hurried and grabbed one! This stroller is seriously the best!! So easy to push, very good quality, really nice looking - everything is perfect!
